    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-12T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-12T11:00:00-05:00" n="302"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/2139</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-12T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 12, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 13, 6.31 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2128. In a conversation with Minister of War he informs me that even if Italy’s
                    territory overrun during this war be evacuated <pb facs="0449" n="357"
                        xml:id="pg_357"/> in the event of an armistice, Italy, should armistice
                    fail, would not be able to defend former frontier against sudden attack as that
                    frontier is nearly twice length of Piave frontier and all of Italy’s original
                    defenses on former frontier have been destroyed. To render Italy at all secure
                    against attack, he declares that it is necessary to assign to Italy as pledges
                    certain strategic points to hold during any negotiations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
